whatly (6.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Taskbar unread badge (Unity LauncherEntry), adjustable interface font size,
    optional auto-reload after a page crash, network status in the tray tooltip.
  * HiDPI: QT_SCALE_FACTOR scales the web content; WHATLY_MAX_FPS lifts the FPS
    cap. Build a dictionary subset with -DWHATLY_DICTIONARIES.
  * Optional Windows code signing via SignPath Foundation.
  * See CHANGELOG.md for the full list.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

whatly (6.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Native notifications now use a high-resolution app icon, so the logo no
    longer looks blurry on desktops with large notification popups such as
    Cinnamon on Linux Mint (issue #2).
  * See CHANGELOG.md for the full list.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0200

whatly (6.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rebrand WhatSie -> Whatly with a new teal identity.
  * Multiple accounts, chat themes, privacy blur, multi-language spell check,
    app lock, connection watchdog, native Windows support and more.
  * See CHANGELOG.md for the full list.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0200
